  "prompt": "What are the names of famous entrepreneurs in Gulf?",
  "response": "Several notable entrepreneurs from the Gulf region have made significant contributions to various industries. Here are some prominent names:\n\n1. **Majid Al Futtaim** - Founder of majid al-futtaim Group, a leading retail and leisure conglomerate in the Middle East.\n  \n2. **Mohammad Al Habtoor** - Chairman of the Al Habtoor Group, which has interests in hospitality, automotive, and real estate.\n\n3. **Khalaf Al Habtoor** - The founding chairman of the Al Habtoor Group, involved in various industries including real estate and hospitality.\n\n4. **Rakesh Jhunjhunwala** - A prominent investor who, while based in India, has significant investments in Gulf businesses.\n\n5. **Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum** - Vice President and Prime Minister of the UAE and Ruler of Dubai, known for his initiatives in entrepreneurship and innovation.\n\n6. **Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan** - Crown Prince of Abu Dhabi, who has promoted economic diversification and entrepreneurship in the UAE.\n\n7. **Sultan Ahmed bin Sulayem** - Chairman of Dubai Ports World (DP World), a global leader in logistics and port operations.\n\n8. **Fahad Alrajhi** - A prominent figure in Saudi Arabia known for his work in the investment sector.\n\n9. **Khalid Al-Mansoori** - Founder of various businesses in the UAE focusing on technology and innovation.\n\n10. **Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan** - While he passed away in 2004, his initiatives and vision for economic development have profoundly influenced entrepreneurship in the UAE.\n\nThese entrepreneurs have played significant roles in economic development across various sectors including real estate, hospitality, logistics, and technology.",
